{"name": "click-complete-fig", "metadata": {"name": "click-complete-fig", "version": "1.1.1", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/withfig/autocomplete-tools", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["click"], "summary": "Autogenerate Completions for CLI tools built with click", "upload_time": 1658244309}, "documentation": ["## Autogenerate Completions for CLI tools built with `click`\n\n\nAdd the integration to your CLI tool:\n\n```bash\npip install click_complete_fig\n```\n\nAdd new subcommand to your CLI tool.\n- You must pass in the root level CLI.\n- The `add_completion_spec_command` function will add a new `generate-fig-spec` to the passed in `cli`\n\n```python\nfrom click_complete_fig import fig\n\n@click.group()\ndef cli():\n    pass\n\nfig.add_completion_spec_command(cli)\n```\n\nYou can now automatically generate the completion spec skeleton by running the following command:\n\n```bash\n$CLI generate-fig-spec > $CLI.ts\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "click_complete_fig", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "click_complete_fig.fig", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "click_complete_fig.fig.add_completion_spec_command", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cli", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "click_complete_fig.fig.generate_completion_spec", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cli", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "click_complete_fig.fig.get_value", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "dict", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "keys", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "click_complete_fig.fig.flat_map", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "fn", "type": null, "de